# Privacy Policy (English)

Effective Date: January 1, 2020  
Last Updated: May 1, 2026

Introduction

This Privacy Policy describes how 「爱应用(iApp)」(“iApp”, “we”, “us”) handles personal information when you use our mobile application and related services (the “Services”) in regions where European or United States privacy frameworks may apply, including where the EU General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”), the UK GDPR / UK Data Protection Act, or US state privacy laws (such as the California Consumer Privacy Act / California Privacy Rights Act, “CCPA / CPRA”) apply.

We process personal information lawfully, fairly, and transparently. Where required, we rely on appropriate legal bases such as consent, performance of a contract, legitimate interests (where permitted and balanced against your rights), or legal obligations.

If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the Services.

We may update this Policy. If we make material changes, we will provide notice as required by applicable law (for example, in-app notice or email where appropriate). Continued use after the effective date of updates may constitute acceptance where permitted by law.

1. Categories of Information We Collect

Depending on how you use the Services and your choices, we may collect:

· Account and security-related data: for example, device identifiers needed for account security or fraud prevention, subject to platform capabilities and your permissions.  
· Service, diagnostics, and security data: for example, limited device and app information, app version, logs, and crash data needed to operate, secure, debug, and improve the Services.

We collect personal information only where we have a lawful basis and limit collection to what is reasonably necessary for the stated purposes (data minimization).

2. How We Use Information and Legal Bases (EU / UK)

We may use personal information to:

· Provide, operate, and maintain the Services (contract / steps prior to contract).  
· Secure accounts, detect abuse, prevent fraud, and comply with legal obligations (legal obligation / legitimate interests / security).  
· Improve reliability and performance, including diagnostics where permitted (legitimate interests or consent where required).  
· Communicate with you about security or service-related matters (contract / legitimate interests / legal obligation).

Where consent is required for certain processing (including certain analytics or marketing, where applicable), we will request it separately and you may withdraw consent at any time without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent before withdrawal.

3. App Information, Analytics, and Compliance-Limited Collection

We may process limited application and device information that is necessary to deliver the Services securely and to meet platform requirements from Apple and Google, including requirements related to privacy nutrition labels, permission prompts, and anti-abuse measures.

· We do not use deceptive patterns to expand permissions or trick you into consenting.  
· We align collection with disclosed purposes and, where required, platform disclosure obligations.  
· Where optional analytics or similar technologies are used, we will provide controls or notices consistent with applicable law and platform rules.

If a feature is not necessary for the core Service, we will treat it as optional where legally required and obtain consent when consent is the appropriate legal basis.

4. Sharing and Processors

We may share personal information with:

· Service providers / processors who assist us with hosting, analytics (where permitted), customer support, security, or infrastructure, bound by contracts requiring appropriate safeguards.  
· Authorities when required by law or to protect rights, safety, and security.  
· Corporate transactions (for example, merger or acquisition) subject to legal requirements and safeguards.

We do not sell personal information as “sell” is defined under the CCPA / CPRA, and we do not sell personal information for money without offering applicable opt-out rights where required.

5. International Transfers

If personal information is transferred outside your region (for example, from the EEA, UK, or Switzerland to other countries), we will implement appropriate safeguards required by applicable law, such as Standard Contractual Clauses or equivalent mechanisms, plus supplementary measures where required.

6. Retention

We retain personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes described in this Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. After retention ends, we delete or anonymize information where feasible.

7. Security

We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect personal information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure; please protect your credentials.

8. Your Rights (EU / UK / US and other applicable regions)

Depending on where you live, you may have rights such as:

· Access, rectification, erasure, restriction, objection, and data portability (EU / UK).  
· Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.  
· Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (EU / UK).  
· Rights under US state laws, including the right to know, delete, correct, opt out of certain sharing for cross-context behavioral advertising (where applicable), and non-discrimination for exercising rights (CCPA / CPRA and similar laws).

To exercise rights, contact us using the email below. We may need to verify your identity. Authorized agents may submit requests where permitted by law.

9. Children

The Services are not directed to children under the age where parental consent is required in your jurisdiction. If you believe we have collected information from a child without appropriate consent, contact us and we will take appropriate steps.

10. Third-Party Links and Advertising

The Services may contain third-party features, links, or advertisements. Third parties have their own privacy policies. We are not responsible for third-party practices.

11. Automated Decision-Making

We do not use solely automated decision-making that produces legal or similarly significant effects about you, unless we disclose otherwise and provide rights required by law.

12. Contact

Privacy inquiries: AppleOSer@gmail.com

We will respond within a reasonable timeframe. We may ask for limited information to verify your request.

---

Note on scope: The Chinese section above is intended for users in mainland China. The English section is intended for users in the EU, UK, and United States (and similar jurisdictions) and emphasizes mandatory protections and lawful, disclosed collection of app-related information. If both sections are shown in one document, the section that applies to you depends on your region and applicable law.